HEADWORD: Sanguification
<hw>San`gui*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>sanguification</ets>. See <er>Sanguify</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The production of blood; the conversion of
the products of digestion into blood; hematosis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

